docs.abstract: For that to happen, some monuments — and the historical myths they supported — are going to have to come down.
docs.snippet: For that to happen, some monuments — and the historical myths they supported — are going to have to come down.
docs.lead_paragraph: It doesn’t necessarily follow that a nationwide protest over police brutality would, for some, become a reason to take action against Confederate statues and other controversial monuments. But it has. In just the last week, protesters have knocked down Confederate statues in Richmond, Va., Nashville and Montgomery, Ala., as well as monuments to Christopher Columbus in Boston and St. Paul, Minn.

headline.main: To Overturn Trump, We Need to Overturn White Supremacy
headline.print_headline: We Need to Overturn White Supremacy

docs.abstract: The current civil unrest is deeply connected to the racial disparities exposed by the coronavirus crisis. “I’m just as likely to die from a cop as I am from Covid,” one organizer said.
docs.snippet: The current civil unrest is deeply connected to the racial disparities exposed by the coronavirus crisis. “I’m just as likely to die from a cop as I am from Covid,” one organizer said.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When Mike Griffin, a black community organizer in Minneapolis, took to the streets in protest, he was grieving for two black men taken during the turmoil convulsing the country: George Floyd, who died after gasping for air under the knee of a white police officer, and his own godfather, who succumbed to Covid-19.

headline.main: ‘Pandemic Within a Pandemic’: Coronavirus and Police Brutality Roil Black Communities

docs.abstract: Georgia is one of only four states without a bias crime law. This must change.
docs.snippet: Georgia is one of only four states without a bias crime law. This must change.
docs.lead_paragraph: After Ahmaud Arbery was chased down and killed while he was jogging in Glynn County, Ga., investigators say, one of the white men accused of shooting him used a racial slur. In the above video, Wanda Cooper-Jones, Mr. Arbery’s mother, demands that these men be prosecuted not just on charges of killing her son but also for targeting him because of his skin color. Yet as it now stands, that can’t happen: Georgia is one of just four states in the country without a hate crime law.

headline.main: How Was My Son Ahmaud Arbery’s Murder Not a Hate Crime?

docs.abstract: Everyone thinks the industry needs to change. They don’t yet agree on how.

docs.lead_paragraph: On June 1, Tom Ford, the chairman of the Council of Fashion Designers of America, sent a letter to the board about its meeting the next day. He wanted the board to address the Black Lives Matter protests against racial injustice, he said, and systemic racism in the fashion industry.

headline.main: It’s Time to End Racism in the Fashion Industry. But How?
